- BSS size is 0x4003C6D0
- BSS ends at 0x4750C0 + 0x4003C6D0 = 0x404B1790 (this is correct, it wraps around in 32-bit)

Actually, 0x4750C0 + 0x4003C6D0 = 0x404B1790. But 0x404B1790 > 0x7FFFFFFF, so this is in the upper half of the 32-bit address space. This seems wrong.

Wait, let me recalculate: 0x004750C0 + 0x4003C6D0 = 0x404B1790. Yes, this is correct. The BSS section extends from 0x4750C0 to 0x404B1790, which is about 1GB.

